    <stitle>TRW MANUAL STEERING GEAR - LUBRICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>LUBRICATION</title>
        <para>In all installations, the oil filler plug location on the gear housing should be in such a position that
            the lubricant will cover both the worm and output shaft bearings. Thus the filler plug can be used as a lube
            inspection point to assure the proper gear lube level is maintained.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended lubricants.</para>
    </svcproc>
